# Integration test: Macintosh IIsi Floppy Boot
# Boots the IIsi from the System 7.0.1 1.44 MB HD floppy and verifies the
# Finder desktop, exercising the two defining IIsi fixes:
#   1. Egret XPRAM via Read6805/Write6805 ($02/$08) — without it the heap
#      derails on a black-hole MMFlags.
#   2. On-board V8 video reads its frame buffer from the BOTTOM of Bank A
#      (physical 0); system RAM lives in Bank B at physical $04000000.  The OS's
#      24-bit PMMU maps the slot-$E screen base ($FEE08000 / $00E08000) to
#      physical 0 and logical-0 system RAM into Bank B, so QuickDraw's screen
#      writes land in Bank A — not on the vector table (which would reset-loop).
#
# A single fixed instruction budget reaches a stable Finder desktop
# deterministically (like iici-boot): the pre-inserted floppy is mounted and
# booted with no re-insert, now that the SWIM phase-register read-back self-test
# no longer spuriously ejects it.

scheduler.run 370000000

assert ${machine.id == "iisi"} "machine.id != iisi"
assert ${rom.checksum == "36B7FB6C"} "rom.checksum != 36B7FB6C"
assert ${screen.width == 640} "screen.width != 640"
assert ${screen.height == 480} "screen.height != 480"

# Verify the Finder desktop matches the reference (System 7 menu bar, the
# Disk Tools floppy icon, the Trash icon, gray desktop) — rendered by the V8
# straight out of Bank A at physical 0.
screen.match finder.png

quit
